    "body": "## Summary\n\nFix NaN values in dK/dV during variable-length flash attention backward when a batch entry has `seqlen_q == 0`.\n\nThe root cause was three related issues in the CK backward pipeline: missing early-exit when there are no Q tiles to process, and two follow-on compiler register allocation bugs (VGPR reuse and AGPR misallocation) exposed by the early-exit fix. Details: ROCm/rocm-libraries#5790, #5915, #5991.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`csrc/composable_kernel`** — bump submodule from `574c1c12` to `791afc64`\n- **`tests/test_flash_attn_ck.py`** — add `test_flash_attn_bwd_varlen_seqq_zero` regression test (parametrized over dtype, causal, GQA/MHA, head dim)\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pytest tests/test_flash_attn_ck.py::test_flash_attn_bwd_varlen_seqq_zero -v`\n- [x] `pytest tests/test_flash_attn_ck.py -x` (full suite)\n\nTested and passed on MI300X and MI350.",
